# Styling (Unistyles)

- Do **not** use `StyleSheet` from `react-native`. Use `StyleSheet` from `react-native-unistyles` only.
- Do **not** inline style objects for layout or visual styling when a named style would be used; define styles in a **dedicated styles module** next to the component.
- **File layout:** same folder as the screen or component — e.g. `src/pages/Home/index.tsx` and `src/pages/Home/styles.ts`. Shared layout pieces live under `src/components/layout/` (e.g. `AppHeaderBar`). Name the file `styles.ts` unless multiple style modules in one folder require a more specific name.
- **Imports:** the component file imports primitives from `react-native` (`View`, `Text`, etc.); the styles file imports `StyleSheet` from `react-native-unistyles` and exports the result of `StyleSheet.create` (e.g. `export const styles = StyleSheet.create({ ... })`).
- **Design tokens:** semantic colors, spacing, radius, and typography live in [`src/theme`](src/theme). Import [`src/theme/configure`](src/theme/configure) once from the app entry (`App.tsx`). Prefer `StyleSheet.create(theme => ({ ... }))` and use `theme.colors.*`, `theme.spacing`, etc., instead of hard-coded values.
- **Reusable UI:** shared controls live under [`src/components/ui`](src/components/ui) (`Button`, `Input`, `Card`, `Chip`, …) with colocated `styles.ts` per component; prefer them over one-off primitives so visual updates propagate app-wide.
- **Jest:** keep `setupFilesAfterEnv` including `react-native-unistyles/mocks` so tests do not load the Nitro native StyleSheet.

```tsx
// index.tsx — no StyleSheet from react-native
import { Text, View } from 'react-native';
import { styles } from './styles';
```

```ts
// styles.ts
import { StyleSheet } from 'react-native-unistyles';

export const styles = StyleSheet.create(theme => ({
  container: {
    flex: 1,
    backgroundColor: theme.colors.background,
  },
}));
```
